<TITLE> Stocks finish upbeat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 16 (bdnews24.com) - Stocks rallied Monday after investors rushed to bag shares of pharma major Square Pharmaceuticals inspired by the company's dividend postings. Life insurance stocks, engineering and leather sector along with some banks led the market up. But IT and power and cement stocks went down due to sell offs. Indices fell sharply at the beginning of the day on reports of the arrest of former prime minister and AL president Sheikh Hasina. Security forces arrested Hasina and took her away from her Dhanmondi home at 7:31 am Monday. "The market came back on the Square Pharma dividend announcement," said Salahuddin Ahmed Khan, chief executive of Dhaka Stock Exchange. Square Pharma posted 50 percent cash dividend and 50 percent stock dividend for the year that ended March 31, 2007. The DGEN or general index finished at 2249.40, adding 20.01 points or 0.89 percent. The DSI or all-share price index gained 13.69 points or 0.74 percent to 1843.92. The DSE-20 blue chip index rallied 58.88 points or 3.05 percent to 1986.03. Gainers ruled losers 88 to 86. A total of 28 scrips held steady. The Dhaka Stock Exchange registered an increase in turnover at Tk 1.90 billion from Sunday's Tk 1.65 billion. All the major indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange finished upbeat amid increase in turnover at Tk 286.60 million from Tk 232.60 million. Of the issues traded, 52 gained, 46 lost and eight remained stable on the CSE. On the DSE, Southeast Bank topped the turnover table scoring Tk 173.18 million. It advanced 4.34 percent to Tk 516.25. Second turnover maker BRAC Bank fell 0.53 percent to Tk 786. Square Pharma, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh and Shahjalal Bank were next to BRAC Bank. Square Pharma surged 9.89 percent to Tk 4163.25 following its corporate announcement. A sell-off led Power Grid to lose 1.18 percent to Tk 582. Shahjalal Bank, however, added 4.85 percent to Tk 259. Major gainers were Sandhani Life Insurance, Fareast Life Insurance and Meghna Life 